 <text id="A0102T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Samuel Moses writes his father that he may be able to return home soon.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Charles Moses Back Creak Shenando Augusta County Va, Samuel M Moses <lb/> a prisoner of war
     in Camp Chase <lb/> April 21, 1862
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1862-04-21">April 21, 1862</date>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Dear father</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>I <orig reg="seat">seet</orig> my self to inform you all that I am well and hope those few
      <orig reg="lines">loines</orig> and find you all well. I <orig reg="received">receve</orig>
     your letter dated march the 26. I was glad to <orig reg="hear">here</orig> from you all gave my
     love to mother + Brothers + sisters you wanted to <orig reg="know">no</orig> when I could come
     home I do not <orig reg="know">no</orig> when but I dont think it will be very long I must
     bring my letter to a close <orig reg="by">buy</orig> saying write soon as you get my letter </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>and remember your son until death</salute>
     <signed>Samuel M Moses</signed>
     <seg type="postscript">
      <name type="recipient">To Charles Moses</name>
     </seg>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
